Name Rascal/Expressions/Values/String/NotEqual

Syntax Exp1 != Exp2
Types
Exp1 Exp2 Exp1 != Exp2
str str bool
Description Yields true if both arguments are not identical and false otherwise.
Examples 
rascal>"abc" != "defghi";
bool: true
rascal>"abc" != "abc";
bool: false
